<br>
Thanks in advance,<br>
<br>
Mett 29 DE Enchanter <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rangarth>rangarth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#330000>(3/26/03 4:57:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=169.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question about INT vs. CHA</span><hr size=1> Well for one thing you want at least 110 cha for the best prices at the neutral vendors.<br>
<br>
Second is charisma is used to add to the resistance of a mob breaking from a charm.  <br>
<br>
Other than those 2 things I am not sure how charisma affects spells or npcs.<br>
<br>
But if you plan on charming mobs than you need to get the cha up as well.  Easy ways of doing this is working on jewelcraft and eventually getting you Grandmaster Jewelry Eyeglass which gives 50 cha in a range slot and an opal stein that gives 25 cha.<br>
<br>
There are other ways as well and dont discount your cha buffs at 56 you get a plus 50 buff.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps <p>Rangarth Oakspirit<br>
Druid Healer of Karana<br>
